Array
-----
1. Array is a non-primitive datatype (reference type)
2. Arrays are object in java
3. Arrays are dynamically allocated in java
4. Array works on the concept of indexing
5. Array indexing starts from 0 because it follows number system.
6. Pre-requisite for array allocation is base address 
7. Arrray works on continuous memory allocation
8. Array can holds primitive data type as well as object reference 
9. Array elements shares same name but differentiable by there indexing 
10. Types of array : 
    i. One dimensional array 
    ii.Two dimensional array 
        It have special type of 2d array which is known as Jagged Array
    iii. Multi-dimensional array 
11. Array can holds homogenous data elements (homogenous means same type of data.)

    i. One dimensional array 
    Syntax : 
        <datatype> <array_name>[] = {element1, element2,....., element n};
    Example : 
        int arr[] = {12,23,34,45,56};
        char ch[] = {'a','b','c'}; 
        double per[] = {34.44,56.66,78.88,23.32};
        etc 
    
    Syntax : 
    <datatype> <array_name>[] = new <datatype>[]{element1, element2,....., element n};
    Example : 
        int arr[] = new int[]{12,23,34,45,56};
        char ch[] = new char[]{'a','b','c'}; 
        double per[] = new double[]{34.44,56.66,78.88,23.32};
        etc 
    
    Syntax : 
        <datatype> <array_name>[] = new <datatype>[size];
    Example : 
        int arr[] = new int[5];
        char ch[] = new char[7]; 
        double per[] = new double[10];
        etc 
    